com.paydiant.android.core.service

Interface IPaymentAccountManagerService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PaymentAccountManagerService

    public interface IPaymentAccountManagerService
    The Interface IPaymentAccountManagerService.

    Warning: DO NOT reference the core.service package classes directly as these are missing the required business functionalities. Use core.facade or ui.service classes instead.

    Author:
    Paydiant Inc.

        DetailedPaymentAccount addPaymentAccount(PaymentAccountData paymentAccountData)
        Adds a payment account.

        Parameters:
        paymentAccountData - the payment account data
        Returns:
        the detailed payment account
        Throws:
        PaydiantException - in case of an error occurs, PaydiantException or one of its subclasses with the following status codes will be thrown.

        414 (REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG) - Insufficient Funds in account
        410 (GONE) - Payment Account Already Exists
        426 (UPGRADE_REQUIRED) - Unsupported IIN
        508 (LOOP_DETECTED) - Verification Failed
        421 (DESTINATION_LOCKED) - Add Payment Account Failed
        400 (BAD_REQUEST) - Field Validation failure
        402 (PAYMENT_REQUIRED) - Invalid Card Number
        406 (NOT_ACCEPTABLE) - Invalid Expiration Date
        419 (INSUFFICIENT_SPACE_ON_RESOURCE) - Payment Account Type Mismatch
        420 (METHOD_FAILURE) - Payment Account Network Type Mismatch
        500 (INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR) - Internal Server Error

      • refreshPaymentAccountBalance

        AccountBalance refreshPaymentAccountBalance(String paymentAccountUri)
        Refreshes the payment account balance information.
        Parameters:
        paymentAccountUri - the URI of the payment account that balance needs to be refreshed.
        Returns:
        Payment Account balance information
        Throws:
        PaydiantException - in case of an error occurs, PaydiantException or one of its subclasses with the following status codes will be thrown.

        400 (BAD_REQUEST) - Balance inquiry failed.
        405 (METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED) - Balance temporarily unavailable.
        406 (NOT_ACCEPTABLE) - Balance not supported.
        414 (REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG) - Invalid balance amount.
        500 (INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR) - Server Error
        503 (SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE) - Payment account URI does not exist.
        Since:
        4.0.0.2
